        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-05-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-05-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="326" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d326">
                <head>Municipal Council of Deal</head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Deal, Kent</hi>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-05-06">
                        <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 6, 1865</date>.</dateline>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: At a meeting of the town council for this
                        borough held on Wednesday, the 3d instant, the resolution hereunder written
                        was unanimously carried, and that the same be presented through your good
                        self to the government of the United States.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>EDWARD DREW, </signed>
                    <hi rend="italic">Town Clerk</hi>. </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">C. F. Adams</hi>, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.,
                                &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                    <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“That this council hereby express their sincere regret at the severe
                                loss which the people of the United States have sustained by the
                                untimely death of President Lincoln; that they regard with the
                                utmost horror the crime by which the President’s life was taken and
                                sacrificed, and that on behalf and in the name of the inhabitants of
                                this borough (Deal) they most respectfully offer the government of
                                the United States their sincere and earnest sympathy under the
                                dreadful calamity that has befallen them.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
